# Data Structures in Python

This project contains clean, beginner‑friendly implementations of core data structures and algorithms using Python.
It is designed to demonstrate understanding of computer science fundamentals, problem‑solving, and code organization.

## 📁 Project Structure
data-structures-python/
 │── src/ │
     ├── dynamic_array.py │
     ├── linked_list.py │
     ├── stack.py │
     ├── queue.py │
     ├── sorting.py │
     ├── binary_search.py │
     ├── recursion_examples.py |
 │── tests/ │
    ├── test.py │
 │── README.md │

---
## 🧱 Implemented Data Structures & Algorithms

### 🔹 Dynamic Array
- Resizable array similar to Python's built‑in list
- Supports append, indexing, and automatic resizing

### 🔹 Linked List
- Singly linked list
- Node creation, append, and traversal

### 🔹 Stack
- LIFO (Last‑In, First‑Out)
- Push, pop, peek, and empty check

### 🔹 Queue
- FIFO (First‑In, First‑Out)
- Enqueue, dequeue, and empty check

### 🔹 Sorting Algorithms
- Bubble Sort
- Merge Sort

### 🔹 Searching
- Binary Search on sorted lists

### 🔹 Recursion Examples
- Factorial
- Fibonacci

---
## ▶️ How to Run the Code
You can run any file directly: python src/filename.py
Example: python src/linkedList.py
Or run the test file: python tests/test.py

